This paper deals with statistical estimation of latent variables from pairwise comparison data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the topology of the comparison graph, which is a topic in graph theory and network science, making cs.LG and cs.AI the most likely sub-categories. The use of minimax framework and bounds on error rates suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.ST (statistics) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper's focus on pairwise comparisons and ordinal models may make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (social and information networks).
